topic: England's triumphant journey to winning the 2025 Women's Rugby World Cup.
evaluation: This cluster chronicles England's complete journey through the 2025 Women's Rugby World Cup, from an early group stage match (Australia), through quarter-final (Scotland) and semi-final (France), to their ultimate triumph in the final (Canada) and post-victory analysis. All articles are highly relevant, strictly continuous, developmental, and chronologically follow the tournament's progression, offering a comprehensive narrative of their championship win. No articles were de-noised as all contribute significantly to the story.
